### HTTP API Setup
# Start the service with 0x provider settings before running these requests.
# Example:
# SWAP_QUOTE_PROVIDER=0x \
#   SWAP_0X_API_KEY=your_key_here \
#   SWAP_0X_CHAIN_ID=1 \
#   SWAP_0X_TAKER=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000010000 \
#   go run ./cmd/httpapi
# Optional: include "chain_id" in request body to override SWAP_0X_CHAIN_ID for 0x.
# Optional: include "taker" in request body to override the configured SWAP_0X_TAKER for Permit2 quotes.
# Supported 0x chain IDs: 1, 10, 137, 42161, 56
# Supported token symbols: ETH, USDC, DAI, WBTC, USDT

### ETH -> USDC
POST http://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/swaprate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker_from": "ETH",
  "ticker_to": "USDC",
  "amount_from": "0.1"
  ,"chain_id": "1"
}

### ETH -> DAI
POST http://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/swaprate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker_from": "ETH",
  "ticker_to": "DAI",
  "amount_from": "0.1"
  ,"chain_id": "1"
}

### USDC -> USDT
POST http://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/swaprate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker_from": "USDC",
  "ticker_to": "USDT",
  "amount_from": "100"
}

### Example with explicit `taker`
POST http://127.0.0.1:8081/v1/swaprate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "ticker_from": "ETH",
  "ticker_to": "USDC",
  "amount_from": "0.1",
  "chain_id": "1",
  "taker": "0x0000000000000000000000000000000000010000"
}


